.TH "ima_post_read_file" 9 "ima_post_read_file" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ima_post_read_file \- in memory collect/appraise/audit measurement
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ima_post_read_file
.BI "(struct file *file "  ","
.BI "void *buf "  ","
.BI "loff_t size "  ","
.BI "enum kernel_read_file_id read_id "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "file" 12
pointer to the file to be measured/appraised/audit
.IP "buf" 12
pointer to in memory file contents
.IP "size" 12
size of in memory file contents
.IP "read_id" 12
caller identifier
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Measure/appraise/audit in memory file based on policy.  Policy rules
are written in terms of a policy identifier.

On success return 0.  On integrity appraisal error, assuming the file
is in policy and IMA-appraisal is in enforcing mode, return -EACCES.
